metadata.name: Momentary #247
metadata.description:
Sometimes, life's troubles seem to be immense and endless. They make us run around in despair, helplessly looking in every direction in search of an answer.

It's tough to be in control of those situations until we understand that everything in our life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

We tend to forget that life finds its way and that we just need to hold enough to start to see a clear path to follow.

Life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

Hold enough.

There is a path to follow.

-------
WARNING
Please, have into consideration that this work requires some CPU power due to the number of points that needs to be drawn on the canvas. Depending on the hardware and work features, the drawing could take some seconds to some minutes to be finished. 
-------

/- Features

/- Color Scheme
-. Vintage graphite
-. Ashes
-. Serenity
-. Blossom
-. Dark chocolate
-. Blue pen

/- Sky Texture
-. Pencil strokes left
-. Pencil strokes right
-. Pointed lines diagonal
-. Pointed lines vertical
-. Crosshatch
-. Clean

/- Celestial Object
-. Fire burst type A
-. Fire burst type B
-. Eclipse
-. Flare
-. Void

/- Terrain QTY.
-. 1 to 5

/- Terrain Type
-. Blasted sand
-. Peaceful sand
-. Rocky ridges

/- Terrain accent
-. True
-. False

/- Dripping ridges
-. True
-. False

/- Frame
-. True
-. False

-------

/- Controls

[p] Save image @ 2000x2300 px.
[Backspace] Pause the animation.
[Enter] Play the animation. 

-------

metadata.name: fibinous infection #17
metadata.description:
This generative token is based on Fibonacci words.

* Press "s" to save the current image
* Press "h" to stop the animation
* Press "r" to resume the animation

Feature:
* color scheme: 16 variations of sets of 4 colours
* start angle: first direction, between 0 and 360
* step: determines the distance between dots, between 15 and 45
* angle: the angle of each turn, between 85 and 95
* width: determines the size of the dot. Between 1 and 10.
* dots: the number of dots for each cycle

metadata.name: notturno generativo #104
metadata.description:
by fabiello.art

my first generative nft is a nocturnal landscape written in p5.js, where I present my personal fusion of code and figurative art, a vision of hills and trees under a sky of stars and a full moon.
Each iteration presents a number of random variables such as to make the possible night scenarios tend to infinity, each capable of evoking different emotions due to its colors and shapes.

I like to imagine how every possible landscape is somehow connected to a physical or metaphysical place of the personal experience of the beholder. 
The use of the machine and the code, of human thought and its evolution up to our time, as an instrument of discovery and imaginative exploration of territories of the body and the soul.

The code of the trees is derived from J. Poliachik's Generative Trees.
1080x1080 px 
_

https://twitter.com/fabielloart

metadata.name: enter the dragon #11
metadata.description:
This generative token uses a modified fractal algorithm based on the Dragon Curve.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_curve

Random colours and radius are used to visualize the pattern.


color scheme: 14 variations of sets of 4 colours
start angle: first direction, between 0 and 90
loops: how many iterations to pre-compute, between 7 and 15
angle: the angle of each turn, between 85 and 90
frames: total number of frames before the animation stops. Between 2500 and 5000.
alpha: alpha value used for some transparency. Between 200 and 250.

metadata.name: tiredEyes #12
metadata.description:
tired eyes
try to pull me away
but they are just weak little goo balls
with no say so

while homunculus puppeteers

- strings pulled
- fate sealed
- stage set

"the show just started.
youre not leaving."

ok. one more hour.
but thats it.


created with hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

four features:
"iris" - six eye color palette outputs (brown / blue / green / hazel / grey / purple)
"sclera" - five eye health color palette outputs (healthy / normal / strained / high / insomniac)
"stimuli" - six background color palette outputs (retro / fresh / dark / purple / fire / bnw)
"energy" - five outputs controlling background oscillator frequency and feel (chill / responsive / flow / hyperfocus / delirious)

900 total possible feature combinations
added randomness in iris and background for uniqueness. low but non-zero possibility of minting the same feature set.

metadata.name: Crypto Chapeletas 2112021 #20
ALL SEEING #36
metadata.description:
ALL SEEING explores the distribution of human eye colors by mapping color probabilities to each mint. Every artwork is different. Eye positioning, color, stroke and density is determined by a random seed hash. Color probability is loosely based on distribution across the human population, but weighted slightly to allow more color drops. For a lucky few, eyes become multicolored. If the hash gives it's blessing, there's a STAR MAN waiting in that rarest ~1% of mints that features a red background and a near fully-dialated pupil.

--- Features ---
Random eye color distributions of brown ~51% ,blue ~20%, hazel ~10%, amber ~5%, gray ~5%, green ~5%, heterochromia ~3%, and STAR MAN ~1%
Color density
White density
